$ /sys

The → Linux/filesystem/sysfs filesystem is usually mounted on `/sys`. It contains information about → Linux/block-device[block devices] (→ Linux/fhs/sys/block) and other kernel stuff.

Every registered → Linux/kernel/kobject creates a directory in or under `/sys`.

sa:

  → Linux/fhs/sys/bus
    -
  → Linux/fhs/sys/class
    -
  → Linux/fhs/sys/dev
    -
  → Linux/fhs/sys/devices
    -
  → Linux/fhs/sys/firmware
    -
  → Linux/fhs/sys/fs
    -
  → Linux/fhs/sys/kernel
    -
  → Linux/fhs/sys/module
    -
  → Linux/fhs/sys/power

